From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gnoblin Developers <gnoblin@example.invalid>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 04:10:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] tests: ignore input enters for unwrapped Wayland surfaces

Some Wayland test clients use the shared WaylandDisplay helper while
also creating raw wl_surface resources directly. These surfaces do not
have a WaylandSurface wrapper stored in wl_surface user data, but the
shared seat listeners can still receive pointer or keyboard enter events
for them.

Ignore those enter events instead of emitting a GObject signal on a NULL
instance. This keeps G_DEBUG=fatal-criticals useful for real compositor
criticals while avoiding a false abort in tests such as
/wayland/subsurface/parent-unmapped.
---
 src/tests/wayland-test-clients/wayland-test-client-utils.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/tests/wayland-test-clients/wayland-test-client-utils.c b/src/tests/wayland-test-clients/wayland-test-client-utils.c
index 99d2116..3881416 100644
--- a/src/tests/wayland-test-clients/wayland-test-client-utils.c
+++ b/src/tests/wayland-test-clients/wayland-test-client-utils.c
@@ -245,6 +245,9 @@ pointer_handle_enter (void              *user_data,
 {
   WaylandSurface *surface = wl_surface_get_user_data (surface_resource);
 
+  if (!surface)
+    return;
+
   g_signal_emit (surface, surface_signals[SURFACE_POINTER_ENTER],
                  0, pointer, serial);
 }
@@ -311,6 +314,9 @@ wl_keyboard_enter (void               *user_data,
 {
   WaylandSurface *surface = wl_surface_get_user_data (surface_resource);
 
+  if (!surface)
+    return;
+
   g_signal_emit (surface, surface_signals[SURFACE_KEYBOARD_ENTER],
                  0, keyboard, serial);
 }
